  <TITLE>Shipping plugins should properly handle products marked as &quot;free shipping&quot;</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>Intro: Shipping plugin developers should not manually handle such products. Let's just not pass them to plugins. We can filter them in the &quot;CreateShippingOptionRequests&quot; method of &quot;ShippingService&quot;. Handle properly if all items are free. Or even of some are free (multiple requests) - ensure no empty requests are created. Otherwise, it can cause issues in plugins. Ensure that estimate shipping works fine when all items are free. On the other hand, it'll cause issues when we have, for example, a &quot;free shipping&quot; product but with not &quot;free shipping&quot; associated product. So maybe, it's better to leave for plugin developers to handle it Let's do in our built-in plugins</DESCRIPTION>
  <REPONAME>nopCommerce</REPONAME>
  <TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>265</TIMEDIFFERENCEDAYS>
